I"ƒ<p>The <code>niko_home_control</code> platform allows you to integrate your <a href="https://www.niko.eu/enus/products/niko-home-control">Niko Home Control</a> into Home Assistant.</p>
<h2>Configuration</h2>
<p>To enable this lights, add the following lines to your <code>configuration.yaml</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
light:
  - platform: niko_home_control
    host: IP_ADDRESS
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='host' href='#host'></a> host</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>The IP address of the Niko Home light.</p>
</span></p></dd></dl>
</div>
